<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1622,1901]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1695,1721]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks.</emphasis>
Sexual females were described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dettmer, H. S. J." box="[723,902,1695,1721]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="123 - 132" refId="ref43442" refString="Dettmer, H. S. J. (1934) Vier neue Neuroterus - Arten aus Japan. Broteria, 3, 123 - 132." type="journal article" year="1934">Dettmer (1934)</bibRefCitation>
. Later, Monzen redescribed the sexual generation, including the males (
<bibRefCitation author="Monzen, K." box="[440,600,1730,1757]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="24 - 38" refId="ref48573" refString="Monzen, K. (1954) Revision of the Japanese gall wasps with the descriptions of new genus, subgenus, species and subspecies (II). Cynipidae (Cynipinae) Hymenoptera. Annual Reports of Gakugei Faculty of Iwate University, 6, 24 - 38." type="journal article" year="1954">Monzen 1954</bibRefCitation>
). The asexual generation was described based only on the galls (
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda 1996</bibRefCitation>
). The sexual (C-101) and the asexual (C-092) generations were linked experimentally by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda (1996)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1622,1901]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1838,1864]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Biology.</emphasis>
The catkin galls of the sexual generation and the detachable leaf galls of the asexual generation both develop on 
<taxonomicName box="[282,436,1875,1901]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutissima">
<emphasis box="[282,436,1875,1901]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Q. acutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[490,631,1875,1901]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[490,631,1875,1901]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Q. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[706,778,1875,1901]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Cerris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[706,778,1875,1901]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Cerris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (Table 1; 
<bibRefCitation author="Monzen, K." box="[900,1058,1874,1901]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="24 - 38" refId="ref48573" refString="Monzen, K. (1954) Revision of the Japanese gall wasps with the descriptions of new genus, subgenus, species and subspecies (II). Cynipidae (Cynipinae) Hymenoptera. Annual Reports of Gakugei Faculty of Iwate University, 6, 24 - 38." type="journal article" year="1954">Monzen 1954</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Melika, G. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Abe, Y. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Nicholls, J. &amp; Wachi, N. &amp; Ide, T. &amp; Yang, M. - M. &amp; Penzes, Zs &amp; Csoka, G. &amp; Stone, G. N." box="[1070,1280,1875,1901]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 79" refId="ref47700" refString="Melika, G., Pujade-Villar, J., Abe, Y., Tang, C. - T., Nicholls, J., Wachi, N., Ide, T., Yang, M. - M., Penzes, Zs, Csoka, G. &amp; Stone, G. N. (2010) Palaearctic oak gallwasps galling oaks (Quercus) in the section Cerris: re-appraisal of generic limits, with descriptions of new genera and species (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). Zootaxa, 2470 (1), 1 - 79. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2470.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">
Melika 
<emphasis box="[1156,1213,1875,1901]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
